			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok,lets make this easy and cheap,wear int inc.. items when you practice fletch, you'll learn quicker and have less fails. Start with the cheapest of each component,field points,large nocks, wood shafts, and round fletches. Do them till you trivial, it will say this is trivial for someone of you skill. Then upgrade one componant, the one that is the next least expensive, and do that till it is trivial,then repeat. Always use three basic componants and the next most expensive, when trying to icrease your skill because it's cheaper and only the single most expensive component set the lvl of difficulty. Save mixtures of higher priced components for the arrows that you are going to use yourself. Also vanes are high end fletches used in make high end arrows. As for bows when you trivial parabolic fletches you will be able to make hickory bows with little chance of failing, components are hickory stave, one of either hemp twine, linen string, or silk string. The better the string the the less dly the bow has , but also the less the dmg. hickorey cannot be plained/for shaped or whittled/for carved,both of which makes bows faster but takes away some dmg. Elm can be carved but not shaped, recomend skill lvl 70. Ash can be plained or shaped, recomend lvl 125. Oak can be plained or shaped, and you can add 1 cam which makes bow faster but less dmg, recomend lvl 150. Darkwood can be plained or shaped and can be made with 2 cams which results in a compound bow. And yes cams in the real world increase dmg but this is not the real world is it ?...lolps I will let you guess at what lvl to try darkwood, lol oops there went a chunk of plat on that failed attempt lol.Here are base stats for the components of bows. <BR>
Hickory dmg 10 rng 50 Hemp twine no mod..  <BR>
Elm     dmg 13 rng 75 Linen string -1dmg fast dly<BR>
Ash     dmg 16 rng 100 Silk string -2dmg faster&quot;<BR>
Oak     dmg 21 rng 125 Whitt blade -1dmg fast  &quot;<BR>
Dark    dmg 25 rng 150 Plainer     -2dmg faster&quot;<BR>
1Cam -1dmg fast dly<BR>
2Cams-2dmg faster dly<BR>
I hope this has been of help to you. If it has please let me know, and happy flethcing!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
